ilks, C. and Karlan, Beth Y. and Lester, Jenny and Orsulic, Sandra and Borowsky, Mark and Cadungog, Mark and Czerwinski, Christine and {Huelsenbeck-Dill}, Lori and Iacocca, Mary and Petrelli, Nicholas and Rabeno, Brenda and Witkin, Gary and {Nemirovich-Danchenko}, Elena and Potapova, Olga and Rotin, Daniil and Berchuck, Andrew and Birrer, Michael and DiSaia, Phillip and Monovich, Laura and Curley, Erin and Gardner, Johanna and Mallery, David and Penny, Robert and Dowdy, Sean C. and Winterhoff, Boris and Dao, Linda and Gostout, Bobbie and Meuter, Alexandra and Teoman, Attila and Dao, Fanny and Olvera, Narciso and Bogomolniy, Faina and Garg, Karuna and Soslow, Robert A. and Levine, Douglas A. and Abramov, Mikhail and Bartlett, John M. S. and Kodeeswaran, Sugy and Parfitt, Jeremy and Moiseenko, Fedor and Clarke, Blaise A. and Goodman, Marc T. and Carney, Michael E. and Matsuno, Rayna K. and Fisher, Jennifer and Huang, Mei and Kimryn Rathmell, W. and Thorne, Leigh and Van Le, Linda and Dhir, Rajiv and Edwards, Robert and Elishaev, Esther and Zorn, Kristin and Broaddus, Russell and Goodfellow, Paul J. and Mutch, David and Schultz, Nikolaus and Liu, Yuexin and Akbani, Rehan and Cherniack, Andrew D. and Cerami, Ethan and Weinhold, Nils and Shen, Hui and Hoadley, Katherine A. and Kahn, Ari B. and Bell, Daphne W. and {The Cancer Genome Atlas Research Network} and {Genome sequencing centres: Broad Institute} and {Washington University in St Louis} and {Genome characterization centres: British Columbia Cancer Agency} and {Broad Institute} and {Harvard Medical School/Brigham \& Women's Hospital/MD Anderson Cancer Center} and {University of North Carolina} and {University of Southern California \& Johns Hopkins} and {Genome data analysis centres: Broad Institute} and {Institute for Systems Biology} and {Memorial Sloan-Kettering Cancer Center} and {University of California}, Santa Cruz/Buck Institute and {The University of Texas MD Anderson Cancer Center} and {Biospecimen core resource: Nationwide Children's Hospital} and {Tissue source sites: Asterand} and {British Columbia Cancer Agency} and {Cedars-Sinai Medical Center} and {Christiana Care} and {Cureline} and {Duke University} and {Gynecologic Oncology Group} and {International Genomics Consortium} and {Mayo Clinic} and {N. N. Blokhin Russian Cancer Research Center} and {Ontario Tumour Bank} and {St Petersburg Academic University} and {University Health Network} and {University of Hawaii} and {University of Pittsburgh} and {Washington University School of Medicine} and {Disease analysis working group}},
  year = 2013,
  month = may,
  journal = {Nature},
  volume = {497},
  number = {7447},
  pages = {67--73},
  issn = {1476-4687},
  doi = {10.1038/nature12113},
  abstract = {We performed an integrated genomic, transcriptomic and proteomic characterization of 373 endometrial carcinomas using array- and sequencing-based technologies. Uterine serous tumours and {$\sim$}25\% of high-grade endometrioid tumours had extensive copy number alterations, few DNA methylation changes, low oestrogen receptor/progesterone receptor levels, and frequent TP53 mutations. Most endometrioid tumours had few copy number alterations or TP53 mutations, but frequent mutations in PTEN, CTNNB1, PIK3CA, ARID1A and KRAS and novel mutations in the SWI/SNF chromatin remodelling complex gene ARID5B. A subset of endometrioid tumours that we identified had a markedly increased transversion mutation frequency and newly identified hotspot mutations in POLE. Our results classified endometrial cancers into four categories: POLE ultramutated, microsatellite instability hypermutated, copy-number low, and copy-number high. Uterine serous carcinomas share genomic features with ovarian serous and basal-like breast carcinomas. We demonstrated that the genomic features of endometrial carcinomas permit a reclassification that may affect post-surgical adjuvant treatment for women with aggressive tumours.},
  file = {/Users/guluthefish/MEGA/zotero/Levine - 2013 - Integrated genomic characterization of endometrial carcinoma.pdf}
}

